        "headline": "Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 7 at 10:45PM CDT until June 7 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND",
        "description": "At 1045 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of\nSawyer, or 12 miles east of Minot, moving northeast at 45 mph.\n\nHAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.\n\nSOURCE...Radar indicated.\n\nIMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.\n\nThis severe thunderstorm will be near...\nSurrey around 1050 PM CDT. Granville around 1100 PM CDT.\n\nOther locations impacted by the severe thunderstorm include Norwich\nand Simcoe.",
        "instruction": "Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from\nwindows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.",
