        "headline": "Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 7 at 10:31PM CDT until June 7 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND",
        "description": "At 1031 PM CDT /931 PM MDT/, severe thunderstorms were located along\na line from near Wing to 7 miles east of Cannon Ball, or along a line\nfrom 29 miles northeast of Bismarck to 14 miles northwest of Linton,\nmoving east at 50 mph.\n\nHAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and small hail.\n\nSOURCE...Bismarck airport ASOS reported a 68 mph gust at 10 pm CDT.\n\nIMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile\nhomes, roofs, and outbuildings.\n\nLocations impacted include...\nBismarck, Mandan, Linton, Lincoln, Steele, Wilton, Center,\nStrasburg, Hazelton, Flasher, Fort Yates, Selfridge, Menoken, Wing,\nSterling, Solen, Tuttle, Hague and Westfield.",
